    <h3>README.md</h3>
    <div class="container-fluid">
      <div class="container-fluid file_content">
        <div class="content_html">

<h1>
kv 1.0</h1>
<p>
Status : development.</p>
<h2>
Synopsis</h2>
<p>
  <img src="https://git.kmx.io/kmx.io/kv/_blob/master/doc/kv-1.0.jpg" alt="kv-1.0.jpg" />
</p>
<h2>
Specification</h2>
<pre><code>     KV : SP* K SP* &#39;:&#39; SP* V SP*

     M1 : KV (&#39;,&#39; KV)* &#39;,&#39;? SP*

     M2 : SP* &#39;{&#39; M1 &#39;}&#39; SP*

     M3 : SP*

      M : M2 | M1 | M3

K1 = V1 : ([^&lt;{}:,&quot;\s][^{}:,&quot;\s]*)

K2 = V2 : &#39;&quot;&#39; (Q | [^&quot;\\\s])* &#39;&quot;&#39;

      Q : &#39;\&quot;&#39; | &#39;\\&#39; | &#39;\n&#39; | &#39;\r&#39; | &#39;\t&#39; | &#39;\v&#39; | &#39;\0&#39;

K3 = V3 : &#39;&quot;&quot;&quot;&#39; \n (.*?) &#39;&quot;&quot;&quot;&#39;

K4 = V4 : &#39;&lt;&lt;&#39; D \s (.*?) D

     V5 : M2

      K : K1 | K2 | K3 | K4
      
      V : V1 | V2 | V3 | V4 | V5</code></pre>
<h2>
Parser</h2>
<p>
The parser will emit events for KV.</p>
<h2>
Command line interface</h2>
<h3>
Usage</h3>
<pre><code>kv --get FILE [...] &lt;&lt;EOF
A, B.B1, C.&quot;C1&quot;.C2
EOF</code></pre>
<p>
Will output concatenated values of files for keys A, B.B1 and C.C1.C2.
Keys must be quoted according to K1 or K2.</p>
<pre><code>  kv --quote FILE [...]</code></pre>
<p>
Will quote files according to (K1 | K2 | K3 | K4) whichever is best.</p>
<pre><code>  kv --unquote FILE [...]</code></pre>
<p>
Will unquote files according to (K1 | K2 | K3 | K4).</p>
<h2>
Reference implementation</h2>
<p>
The reference implementation of kv is implemented in ANSI C.</p>
